  sectionId (47135)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title [Repealed.].
  content `[Repeal of Acts].--Rep. by the Repealing Act, 1870 (14 of 1870), s. 1 and the Schedule, Part II.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_00008_185108_1523264886492&sectionId=47135&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_00008_185108_1523264886492
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_1_a:
  sectionId (47136)
  sectionNo 1A
  orderNo 2
  title Extent.
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by the A.O. 1937.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_00008_185108_1523264886492&sectionId=47136&sectionno=1A&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_00008_185108_1523264886492
obj_root_law_sections_1_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[1A. Extent.--This Act extends to the territories administered on the fourth of July, eighteen`
  line `hundred and fifty-one, by the Governor of the Presidency of Fort William in Bengal, the LieutenantGovernor of North-Western Provinces of Bengal and the Governor of the Presidency of Fort St. George in`
  line Council.]
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (47137)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power to cause levy of tolls on roads and bridges within certain rates, and to appoint collectors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_00008_185108_1523264886492&sectionId=47137&sectionno=2&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_00008_185108_1523264886492
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `^1[The State Government] may cause such rates of toll,`
  line `^2*** as`
  line `^3[it thinks fit], to be levied upon any road or bridge which has been, or shall hereafter be, made or`
  line `repaired ^4[at the expense of the Central or any State Government]; and may place the collection of such`
  line `tolls under the management of such persons as may appear to ^5[it] proper: and all persons employed in the management and collection of such tolls shall be liable to the same responsibilities as would belong to`
  line `them if employed in the collection of the land revenue.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of section 2.--In section 2 of the Indian Tolls Act, 1851(8 of 1851) in its application to`
  line `the State of Orissa, for the words "at the expense of the Central or any State Government", the words "at`
  line `the expense of the Central or any State Government or any Corporation, Statutory Body, Company, Firm`
  line `or person authorized by the State Government for this purpose" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Orissa Act 7 of 1999, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs., ibid., for "The Governor of the Presidency of Fort William in Bengal, the Lieutenant-Governor of the North-Western`
  line `Provinces of Bengal and the Governor of the Presidency of Fort St. George in Council". The words "and the Governor of the`
  line `Presidency of Bombay in Council" had been rep. by Act 8 of 1888, s. 5.`
  line
  line `The authority of the Provincial Government in any Province of India not specified in s. 1A to which this Act and the Indian`
  line `Tolls Act, 1864 (15 of 1864), may be or have been extended, is to be the same as if it had been originally specified in s. 2. See`
  line `the Indian Tolls Act, 1888 (8 of 1888), s. 2(1).`
  line
  line `2. The words "not exceeding the rates mentioned in the Schedule annexed to this Act" omitted by Act 38 of 1920, s. 2 and`
  line `the First Schedule.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "they respectively think fit".`
  line
  line `4. Subs., ibid., for "at the expense of the Govt.".`
  line
  line `5. Subs., ibid., for "them".`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (47138)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 4
  title `Their powers for recovery of toll.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_00008_185108_1523264886492&sectionId=47138&sectionno=3&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_00008_185108_1523264886492
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In case of non-payment of any such toll on demand, the`
  line `officers appointed to collect the same may seize any of the carriages or animals on which it is chargeable,`
  line `or any part of their burden of sufficient value to defray the toll; and, if any toll remains undischarged for`
  line `twenty-four hours, with the cost arising from such seizure, the case shall be brought before the officer`
  line `appointed to superintend the collection of the said toll, who may sell the property seized for discharge of`
  line `the toll, and all expenses occasioned by such non-payment, seizure and sale, and cause any balance that`
  line `may remain to be returned, on demand, to the owner of the property; and the said officer, on receipt of the`
  line `property, shall forthwith issue a notice that, at noon of the next day, exclusive of Sunday, or any closed`
  line `holiday, he will sell the property by auction:`
  line
  line `Release of seized property on tender of dues.--Provided that, if, at any time before the sale has`
  line `actually begun, the person whose property, has been seized shall tender the amount of all the expenses`
  line `incurred, and of double the toll payable by him, the said officer shall forthwith release the property`
  line seized.
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (47139)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 5
  title `Exemptions from payment of toll.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. The words "of troops and military stores and equipages on their march or" rep. by Act 2 of 1901, s. 8 and the Schedule.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_00008_185108_1523264886492&sectionId=47139&sectionno=4&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_00008_185108_1523264886492
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `No tolls shall be paid for the passage ^1*** of Police-officers`
  line `on duty, or of any person or property in their custody, but no other exemption from payment of the toll`
  line `levied under this Act shall be allowed.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Orissa.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 4.--In section 4 of the Indian Tolls Act, 1851 (8 of 1851), in its application`
  line `to the State of Orissa, after the words “shall be paid for the passage of” the words “the State Government`
  line `Vehicles on Government duty and” shall be inserted.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Orissa Act 13 of 1987, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (47140)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title `Assistance of collectors by Police-officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_00008_185108_1523264886492&sectionId=47140&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_00008_185108_1523264886492
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `All Police-officers shall be bound to assist the tollcollectors, when required, in the execution of this Act; and, for that purpose, shall have the same power`
  line `which they have in the exercise of their common police-duties.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (47141)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Penalty for offences under Act. Compensation to person aggrieved. Saving of his right to sue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. The words "of the Zillah" rep. by Act 12 of 1876, s. 1 and the Schedule, Part. I.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_00008_185108_1523264886492&sectionId=47141&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_00008_185108_1523264886492
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Every person, other than the persons appointed to collect the tolls under this Act, who shall levy or`
  line `demand any toll on any public road or bridge, or for passing through any bazar situated thereon, and also`
  line `every person who shall unlawfully and extortionately demand, or take any other or higher toll than the`
  line `lawful toll, or under colour of this Act seize or sell any property knowing such seizure or sale to be`
  line `unlawful, or in any manner unlawfully extort money or any valuable thing from any person under colour`
  line `of this Act, shall be liable on conviction before a Magistrate to imprisonment for any term not exceeding`
  line `six calendar months, or to fine not exceeding two hundred rupees, any part of which fine may be awarded`
  line `by the Magistrate to the person aggrieved; but this remedy shall not be deemed to bar or affect his right to`
  line `have redress by suit in the Civil Court ^1***.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (47142)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Exhibition of table of tolls, and statement of penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_00008_185108_1523264886492&sectionId=47142&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_00008_185108_1523264886492
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `A table of the tolls authorized to be`
  line `taken at any toll-gate or station shall be put up in a conspicuous place near such gate or station legibly`
  line `written or printed in English words and figures, and also in those of the vernacular language of the`
  line `district, to which shall be annexed, written or printed in like manner, a statement of the penalties for`
  line `refusing to pay the tolls and for taking any lawful toll.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (47143)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Application of proceeds of tolls.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_0_00008_185108_1523264886492&sectionId=47143&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_0_00008_185108_1523264886492
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The tolls levied under this Act shall be deemed public revenue`
  line ^1***.
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "but the net proceeds thereof shall be applied wholly to the construction, repair and maintenance of roads and`
  line `bridges within the presidency in which they are levied" omitted by the A.O. 1937.`
